      "id": "msg_012",
      "timestamp": "2024-10-27T10:08:15Z",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I found the issue! You're manually escaping special characters before passing to bcrypt.compare(). This is causing double-escaping. Bcrypt handles special characters correctly on its own.\n\nThe fix is to remove this manual escaping and let bcrypt do its job.",
      "metadata": {
        "model": "claude-sonnet-4.5",
        "tokens": 67
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "msg_013",
      "timestamp": "2024-10-27T10:08:45Z",
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Oh! So we should just pass the raw password to bcrypt.compare()?",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "msg_014",
      "timestamp": "2024-10-27T10:09:00Z",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Exactly! Bcrypt is designed to handle any characters safely. Let me update the code.",
